I would be cautious accepting responses from a box as gospel.  I have had contradictory responses about religion come through, but then again, I align myself much closer with atheism than christianity.  

Many times I feel that the boxes tell us what we want to hear.  Why? I could not tell you.  It could be spirits playing with our heads, or, it could be a piece of our unconscious coming through the radio.  This does happen, I have recorded the voices of people in the same room with me coming through with the same speech patterns (although this happened twice with a Shack hack but I haven&#39;t had it happen with my Minibox yet).  

So in short, if you ascribe to a belief and keep asking pointed questions about that belief over and over, do not be surprised when you hear what you believe coming through the box.

Tim

